    <section class="section">
      <h2>Service Styles</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Buffet</h3>
        <p>Self-service where guests choose from a spread of dishes. Ideal for large gatherings.</p>
        <span class="learn-more" onclick="toggleDetails(this)">Learn More</span>
        <div class="details">Buffet service encourages interaction and offers a wide variety of choices. It's commonly used at weddings and casual events.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>American</h3>
        <p>Plated service where guests are served individually at their tables.</p>
        <span class="learn-more" onclick="toggleDetails(this)">Learn More</span>
        <div class="details">American service emphasizes portion control and aesthetics. It’s popular in restaurants and banquets.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>French</h3>
        <p>Formal service with tableside preparation or presentation by staff.</p>
        <span class="learn-more" onclick="toggleDetails(this)">Learn More</span>
        <div class="details">Used in upscale restaurants, French service highlights elegance and server expertise, such as flambéing or carving.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Russian</h3>
        <p>Food is brought on platters and served by staff directly to guests’ plates.</p>
        <span class="learn-more" onclick="toggleDetails(this)">Learn More</span>
        <div class="details">Russian service is structured and formal, offering refined guest experience. Common at gala dinners.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Banquet Service</h3>
        <p>Pre-plated meals served simultaneously to all guests. Ideal for large functions.</p>
        <span class="learn-more" onclick="toggleDetails(this)">Learn More</span>
        <div class="details">Common in weddings and corporate events, banquet service ensures efficient and uniform delivery of meals.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <div class="approach-block">
        <h3>Student-Centered Learning</h3>
        <p>Hands-on, real-world culinary experiences that build skills and confidence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-block">
        <h3>Inclusive & Diverse</h3>
        <p>Celebrating global cuisines and tailoring services for varied backgrounds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-block">
        <h3>Technology Integration</h3>
        <p>Using VR, AI tools, and interactive content to modernize food education.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-block">
        <h3>Industry Collaboration</h3>
        <p>Partnering with chefs and professionals to ensure practical, relevant learning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="approach-block">
        <h3>Accessibility Commitment</h3>
        <p>Offline options, assistive tools, and inclusive navigation for all learners.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="approach-details">
      <h2>Details of Our Approach</h2>
      <h3>Student-Centered Learning</h3>
      <p>We use practice kitchens, live demos, and simulated environments to prepare students for real-world culinary roles.</p>

      <h3>Inclusive & Diverse</h3>
      <p>Our platform supports multiple languages and highlights international dishes to ensure cultural relevance and inclusivity.</p>

      <h3>Technology Integration</h3>
      <p>Students benefit from virtual kitchen tours, AI feedback, and self-paced interactive modules, accessible on any device.</p>

      <h3>Industry Collaboration</h3>
      <p>We consult industry experts to align our curriculum with trends and best practices in hospitality and food service.</p>

      <h3>Accessibility Commitment</h3>
      <p>We provide screen-reader compatibility, keyboard-friendly layouts, and downloadable materials for every learner.</p>
    </section>

    <footer>
      © 2025 Culinary Service Styles Hub. All rights reserved.
    </footer>
  </div>

  <script>
    function toggleDetails(el) {
      const details = el.nextElementSibling;
      if (details.style.display === 'block') {
        details.style.display = 'none';
        el.textContent = 'Learn More';
      } else {
        details.style.display = 'block';
        el.textContent = 'Show Less';
      }
    }
  </script>
</body>
